        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-11 05:56:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n1.\tException Handling.\n•\tThere are several places that the code ignore exceptions. Mainly in java files BuildHelper and BuildState. I would like to understand why do the code considers these exceptions as one that can be ignored. For example, in BuildHelper there is a catch that ignores IOException. How can we tell between expected IOException and a hardware failure which can also cause this exception?Since the code is a Maven plugin, can it cause a corrupted build?\n•\tForkJoin framework Exception handling. FileReadTask throws an UncheckedIOException. I would like to understand how this exception is caught and handled. \n2.\tMissing Unit Tests.\nAccording to ONAP developer best practices : https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Code+Coverage+and+Static+Code+Analysis ,  we are expected to 70% code coverage. Currently code coverage is 0%. Code coverage must be higher before other progress.\n3.\tForkJoin framework – forkJoinTask documentation states that its primary task is computational tasks. Files reading is a blocking operation, is against the forkJoin guidelines. It fail to enjoy performance optimization this way.  Using NIO should be considered.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
